  "market_context": "Early September 2025; price swept monthly high (≈23800), formed V-shaped reversal with change in state of delivery, establishing bearish daily bias. Analyst anticipated lower move targeting sell-side liquidity using multi-timeframe fractal model.",
  "key_observation": "Monthly high sweep paired with V-shaped reversal and change in state of delivery confirmed a protected swing; candle 3 closure signaled continuation lower, enabling candle 4 bias for short entries into higher-time-frame FVG and PD Array zones.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified monthly high sweep on daily chart (≈23800) followed by V-shaped reversal and confirmed change in state of delivery.",
    "Step 2: Noted candle 3 closure on daily, indicating continuation potential and establishing bearish bias for candle 4.",
    "Step 3: Dropped to 4H to locate higher-time-frame order block and fair value gap near 23550–23600, identifying the zone where wick formation was expected.",
    "Step 4: Used 15-minute chart to find entry opportunities at equal highs (≈23500–23590) with small-wick expansion candles supporting bearish continuation.",
    "Step 5: Evaluated trade timing: preferred candle 3 continuation over later continuations to avoid chasing; used SMT with YM to validate weakness when ES1! entry failed."
  ],
  "outcome": "Two out of three short entries worked; one was stopped out. Target was sell-side liquidity near daily low (≈23200–23370), with 2R+ achievable on successful trades.",
  "lessons": "Blending monthly/daily candle 2-3-4 provides high-probability bias; candle 3 closure confirms continuation; always align lower-time-frame entries with HTF FVG/PD Array and respect mean thresholds; avoid chasing beyond first continuation.",
